<!DOCTYPE html>
<!-- all the information included as comments can be found at mdn web docs, such a great webpage to learn -->
<!-- language to be used should be specified in the html opening tag -->
<html lang="en-us">
<!-- head tag works as a container for meta data (meta data is information about data and is not displayed on the web page --> 
  <head>
<!-- specifies the character encoding (unicode transformation format should be 
     enough for everything) -->
    <meta charset="UTF-8"
<!-- lets the search engine know what the document is about -->
    <meta name="keywords" content="Practicing some html tags" >
  <!-- provides the author's name -->
     <meta name="author" content="Gonzalo F."
</head>
<body>
<!-- embeding an image -->
  <figure>
    <img 
      src="../catedral.jpeg" 
      alter="A lovely sunset at a lovely city in MÃ©xico."
      <!-- Although we shouldn't alter our image size with html attributes, here we have it to practice -->
      heigth="500px"
      width="400px"
      <!--Use of title for images is not recommended(unpredictable screen reader support), always
    better to include such supporting information in the main article text rather than attached to the image -->
      title="Main cathedral in Puebla, finished on 1700's." />
    <!--figcaption lets browsers and assistive technology it describe the other content of the figure-->
    <figcaption> 
      Iconic mexican cathedral, which last 200 years to be built, from 1500 to 1700
    </figcaption>
</body>
</html>
   
